# cursor-proxy environment. Copy to .env, then edit.
# .env is git-ignored (see .gitignore).

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# One or more API keys clients must present. Comma-separated.
# Generate: SK=sk-cp-$(openssl rand -hex 16)
CURSOR_PROXY_API_KEYS=sk-cp-CHANGE-ME

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional — outbound proxy (unlock Claude / GPT / Gemini)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Cursor's backend geo-gates the Anthropic / OpenAI / Google model
# families by request IP. From a CN or HK egress every claude-* /
# gpt-* / gemini-* call returns HTTP 403 "Model not available in
# your region". Set an outbound proxy to a US or EU endpoint to
# unlock those families. See docs/deployment/proxy.md.
#
# Cursor-native models (composer-2.5, grok-4.5-*, kimi-k2.7-code,
# glm-5.2-*) are NOT geo-gated and work without a proxy.
#
# Uncomment ONE of the following:

# HTTPS_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:10808
# HTTPS_PROXY=socks5://user:pass@remote-host:1080
# HTTP_PROXY=$HTTPS_PROXY
# NO_PROXY=localhost,127.0.0.1
